physical_examinations.relevant_findings: A 69-year-old woman developed generalized urticaria after the intake of Tho-mapyrin (250 mg aspirin, 200 mg paracetamol, 50 mg caffeine) two months prior to presentation. She experienced generalized urticaria on six occasions with itching of the palms, lip edema, and dizziness after coffee intake.

A 38-year-old woman with moderate persistent asthma and moderate rhinitis experienced severe anaphylactic shock after an injection of horse antitetanus toxoid serum. She had no prior exposure to horse serum. Skin prick tests were positive for horse, cat, and dog dander extracts.

A 54-year-old man developed generalized pruritus, dyspnea, and sudden hemodynamic shock after intravenous dextran 40 during the resection of a hepatic hydatid cyst. Serum IgE was 34 kU/l with tryptase levels slightly increased to 12.2 Âµg/l following the reaction.

A 33-year-old woman reported anaphylaxis upon latex exposure, with a history of urticaria on contact with latex products. On one occasion, she underwent treatment with oxygen, resulting in rash extension and increased wheeziness.

A 58-year-old amateur fisherman experienced angioedema and urticaria approximately 3 to 8 hours after fishing, attributed to exposure to Galleria mellonella larvae. Skin prick tests showed slight positivity to mites and grass pollen.
